The paper discusses the topic of computer security and intrusion detection systems, which falls under the category of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR). The use of self-organized ant colony algorithms and soft computing paradigms like Decision Trees, Support Vector Machines, and Linear Genetic Programming suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI), "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE), "Learning" (cs.LG), and "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI).
